{{!--
  Tier-4 executable-accounting block. 2026-05-23 curator-rendered-output
  audit: previously rendered inside a collapsed <details>; the ADD formula
  is the primary structural-accounting cue for non-first-class trick pages
  and the curator's audit flagged the collapse as hiding the most important
  data. Now renders expand-by-default as an "ADD"-labeled row, mirroring
  the Notation Summary card's ADD slot.

  Renders only when content.addAnalysis is non-null (= the trick has a
  curator-published resolved formula). Provenance is intentionally NOT
  rendered (curator-internal language).

  Per the 4-tier rendering hierarchy contract: Tier-4 patterns
  (xbody(N), dex(N), stall(N), spin(N), BOD(N), UNS(N), '= N ADD')
  appear ONLY on trick-detail pages + /freestyle/add-analysis; browse
  cards + landing forbid them via test-pinned absence.
--}}
{{#if content.addAnalysis}}
<section class="content-section trick-add-analysis" aria-label="ADD derivation">
  <dl class="trick-add-analysis-fields">
    <dt>ADD</dt>
    <dd><code class="trick-add-analysis-derivation">{{content.addAnalysis.derivation}}</code></dd>
  </dl>
</section>
{{/if}}
